      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Configure heartbeat model fallback policy",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nHeartbeat runs can currently fall through to the normal model fallback chain. For automation-style heartbeat turns, that can replay unattended work through a provider/model policy the heartbeat operator did not intend.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis adds an explicit heartbeat fallback config surface instead of changing default OpenClaw behavior. `heartbeat.fallbacks` is omitted by default, preserving existing fallback resolution. Operators can set `heartbeat.fallbacks: []` to make heartbeat runs fail fast, or provide a heartbeat-specific fallback chain.\n\n## User Impact\n\nExisting configs keep current behavior because omitted `heartbeat.fallbacks` means use normal/default fallback behavior. Users who need strict heartbeat execution can configure:\n\n```yaml\nagents:\n  defaults:\n    heartbeat:\n      model: provider/model\n      fallbacks: []\n```\n\nPer-agent heartbeat config can also override defaults with `agents.list[].heartbeat.fallbacks`.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `pnpm test src/infra/heartbeat-runner.model-override.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-run.media-only.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-utils.test.ts src/config/io.write-prepare.test.ts src/config/heartbeat-config-honor.inventory.test.ts`\n- `pnpm test src/config/schema.base.generated.test.ts src/config/schema.help.quality.test.ts src/config/schema.test.ts src/config/zod-schema.agent-defaults.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core:test`\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nAutoreview was explicitly skipped at user request.\n",
        "branch": "aknight/heartbeat-fallbacks-config",
